</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0073-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0073-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Charles Lee informed Hancock on 27 Feb. 1776 that he intended to contract immediately for four thousand barrels of pork, and a considerable quantity of rum (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ [[Charles Lee]]. &lt;i&gt;The Lee Papers&lt;/i&gt;. 4 vols. New York, 1872-75. In &lt;i&gt;Collections of the New-York Historical Society&lt;/i&gt;, vols. 47. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Lee Papers</span></span>, 1:33032).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0073-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0073-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0047" class="document">General Orders, 14</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0076" class="document">20 April 1776</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0071" class="document">GW to Hancock, this date</a>.</p>

